    "caption": "Short tail, big attitude, master of the middle-of-nowhere.",
    "shortDescription": "Bobcats are the most common wild cat in North America, but most people never see one — they're quiet, cautious, and very good at staying invisible in forests, swamps, and even the edges of towns. Their stubby 'bobbed' tail is where the name comes from. Fun fact: A bobcat can leap three metres in a single bound when it makes its final pounce."
